@NODE "bugs" "Known bugs"

                                   Known bugs
                                  ============

   Documents say that FIB structures must be longword aligned. At the moment,
EasySync allocate FIB structure via standard AllocPooled instead of using
AllocDosObject which do the right alignment (except in two cases). It seems
to work anyway and maybe the longword-align warning is no needed in other system
versions. In anycase if there are troubles that seems to be related to DOS and
FIB, I will fix EasySync. I will fix EasySync's FIB allocs in anycase in future
non-beta versions.

   I am waiting for bug-report... This is a beta version so you (and me too)
have to suppose it is full of unknown bugs even if I hope it is not. For bugs I
do not mean a not-completed feature, but system crashes, severe error while
copying files, files corruption not due to system crashes (caused or not caused
by EasySync) and so on... You know I hope. This beta version do not do several
things it should do --- so it is not a bug if EasySync says that there is an
error on file XXX without specifing path... simply I did not write the code
which gets full path from file... ... ... ... ... ... ... ...

   Possible bug: does not release some lock when exiting on "special"
conditions.

   Refer to source code, -D27 version, in particular read the @{"history" link "hist"} header.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "pack" "Package Contents"

                                Package Contents
                               ==================

   At the moment, this package contains:


  Name
  -------------
  SyncIt/bin/easysync
  SyncIt/bin/easysync.debug
  SyncIt/doc/EasySync.guide
  SyncIt/easysync.prefs
  SyncIt/Icons/easysync.info
  SyncIt/Icons/easysync0.info
  SyncIt/ReadMe.First
  SyncIt/Sources/easysync.a
  SyncIt/Sources/easysyncD21.a
  SyncIt/Sources/easysyncD23.a
  SyncIt/Sources/easysyncD27.a


   SyncIt should be the name of whole future package, fully featured, with
SyncManager, a GUI, several sync-tools and so on... (How far does imagination
go!)

   Bin stores the executable, it is included also the executable with debug
information (and some code/data stripped/changed in order to allow debugging).
You should move this where do you want. Executables (with and without debug
info) refer to -D27 version.

   Doc stores the document, this you are reading.

   In the root of SyncIt there is EasySync.prefs (lowercase) that is an example
of EasySync pref file. You can add a lot of entries. Then move the file in the
same place where you put EasySync executable (it could be another place,
according to tooltype of course)

   Icons stores two rough icons. Use easysync.info and move it where EasySync
executable is. Now, take a look at possible tooltypes. Easysync0.info is given
for historical reasons (I am not a good icon-maker, am I?)

   ReadMe.First suggests you to read this doc before everything else.

   Sources contains the full source code. For historical reasons are packed also
old versions that are not interesting for noone. Reading and testing and
analysis must be done on EasySyncD27.a, then you can trash other versions.
These unuseful old version will be deleted from archive in the future. Now they
remains there because they are the historical steps I did and because this will
be the archive I will keep on my computer...

   Now, if you have read all the contents of this docs, you can try to use
EasySync...

@ENDNODE

